25/05/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- A bus crash near the northern BiH town of Doboj on Saturday (May 24th) claimed the lives of three people and injured 53 others. The bus, which was carrying Croatian pilgrims to a Roman Catholic shrine in Medjugorje, southern Herzegovina, collided with a truck. (RTRS, PBS, DPA, Reuters - 24/05/08) 
